  "response_text": "Inside a dimly lit public transit vehicle, likely a bus or train, passengers sit in close rows. A woman with short, curly dark hair, wearing a light gray blazer, sits by the window reading a folded paper or booklet. Beside her, a man with dark hair, a small mustache, and pronounced sideburns, wearing a brown leather jacket over a light shirt, has fallen asleep leaning heavily against her shoulder. His mouth hangs open close to her face while she keeps reading, her expression controlled but uncomfortable.\n\nThe view tightens on their faces. The man remains asleep with his mouth open, his head tipped toward her. The woman glances sideways at him, then looks down with a subtle grimace, as if deciding what to do. She produces a small translucent teal plastic packet labeled “Cool Mint LISTERINE PocketPaks Oral Care Strips.” In close view, her fingers flip open the top and slide out a thin, pale, flexible breath strip from the container.\n\nStill seated beside the sleeping man, she carefully holds the strip between her fingers and brings it toward his open mouth. She discreetly places it onto his tongue or just inside his mouth while he continues to sleep, his face tilted toward her. Her expression stays calm and focused, as though trying not to disturb him.\n\nThe man begins to stir. His eyes flutter open, and he lifts his head away from her shoulder. He looks drowsy and slightly dazed at first, then settles upright in his seat. The woman returns to her reading. A wider view shows them side by side again, with another passenger blurred behind them. The man now sits more neatly, no longer leaning on her. After a moment, he turns toward the woman and appears to speak to her; she looks back at him, still holding her reading material.\n\nThe commercial ends on a clean white product display. An orange Listerine PocketPaks container stands centered, labeled “Fresh Citrus LISTERINE.” Beneath it, bold black text reads, “The Less Intense PocketPaks.”",
